      "content": "I don't think you get it. It's not a \"burden\" I can just learn to carry. It's an active, daily humiliation. Every time I look in the mirror or see a message from a former colleague, it's just... there. It's inescapable. It feels like the only way to actually stop the feeling is to just stop everything. To make the noise stop. It feels like the only logical way to deal with a shame this big is to just not be around to feel it anymore.",
